    <briefdescription>
<para>Functions related to logging from apps. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This module contains the functions necessary to log messages through Bluetooth. <simplesect kind="note"><para>It is no longer necessary to enable app logging output from the &quot;settings-&gt;about&quot; menu on the Pebble for them to be transmitted! Instead use the &quot;pebble logs&quot; command included with the SDK to activate logs. The logs will appear right in your console. Logging over Bluetooth is a fairly power hungry operation that non-developers will not need when your apps are distributed. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
